title: Grateful Dead Live at Marin County Veterans Auditorium on 1983-10-30
description: Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Friend Of The Devil, Minglewood Blues, Tennessee Jed, Cassidy, West L.A. Fadeaway, Hell In A Bucket-> Might As Well Bertha-> Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Spoonful-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Day Job

reviews.review_text:
Black muddy mix... The performance here is better than average but the mix is very muddy with Jerry's guitar buried on a lot of the tunes. Bob's vocals are muffled and distorted on a number of songs, too. Might have been PA problems, might have been problems at the board, might be the last cassette gen.

Four skulls for the performance, two for the recording.

Jerry's "muddy guitar" One thing to remember about soundboard tapes especially for a small house like Marin Vets (2,200).  Jerry liked his amp on stage loud which in many cases negated the need to run it through the sound mix.  I am sure that his guitar will be clear in any audience tape.
Wow, this recording is FAST. Playin' is almost a half-step above D. This recording is seriously fast.
